tool.name: SingleTransducerImport

param.name: in_conn_file
param.dialogReference:
This is the sde connection file to the UGS SDE, where our tranducer data tables are stored. This is commonly found at:

C:\Users\<User_Name>\AppData\Roaming\ESRI\Desktop10.5\ArcCatalog\

Insert your user name where it says "<User_Name>". The connection file will be a .sde file.

param.name: well_file
param.dialogReference: This is the .xle well file with the well data that you want to import.

param.name: baro_file
param.dialogReference: This is the .xle barometer file with the well data that you want to import.

param.name: startdate
param.dialogReference: This is the day that the transducer was installed and the first manual measurement was taken. This is optional. If you do not fill it in, the script pulls the most recent value from the database for the well.

param.name: enddate
param.dialogReference: This is the day that the transducer was collected and the last manual measurement was taken. This is optional. If you do not fill it in, the script pulls the most recent value from the database for the well.

param.name: startlevel
param.dialogReference: This is the depth to water value of the first manual measurement. Stickup and elevation are accounted for in the script. This is optional. If you do not fill it in, the script pulls the most recent value from the database for the well.

param.name: endlevel
param.dialogReference: This is the depth to water value of the first manual measurement. Stickup and elevation are accounted for in the script. This is optional. If you do not fill it in, the script pulls the most recent value from the database for the well.

param.name: wellname
param.dialogReference: This is the name of the well you are importing data for. The well has to be in the location database before you can import data for it.

tool.summary: This tool imports data from a single transducer into the sde.
tool.usage: Use to remove barometric pressure from nonvented transducers and import them into the sde.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This tool imports data from a single transducer into the sde.
